vectorData.altText: 17. Which of the following terms best describes the movement occurring at the knuckles in the accompanying video?
That's right! Remember, the midline of hand runs through through the middle finger. Movement of the fingers toward the midline of the hand is adduction.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, and then come back to try again.
In the case of the fingers, the “midline” is not the midline of the body, but the midline of the hand, running through the middle finger.
